Normalization Up To BCNF

1. First Normal Form (1NF)
All attributes are atomic (no repeating groups, no multi-valued fields).
Example: Full Name, Address, Phone, Email are single values.
The schema meets the criteria of 1NF.

2.Second Normal Form (2NF)
Rule: There should be no partial dependency (non-key attributes must rely on the entire primary key).
Given that all tables possess single-attribute primary keys (ClientID, LoanID, etc.), partial dependency is absent. 
The schema meets the criteria for 2NF.

3. Third Normal Form (3NF)
Rule: There should be no transitive dependency (non-key attributes relying on other non-key attributes).
Client: Attributes are solely dependent on ClientID. - Loan: Attributes are solely dependent on LoanID.
Repayment: Attributes are solely dependent on RepaymentID.
Saving Account: Attributes are solely dependent on SavingsID.
Transaction: Attributes are solely dependent on TransactionID.
Loan Officer: Concern — ClientID was included, but a loan officer should not be dependent on a client. 
Solution: Eliminate ClientID from the Loan Officer table. The relationship already exists through Loan. 
Following the correction, the schema meets the criteria for 3NF.

4. Boyce–Codd Normal Form (BCNF)
Rule: For every functional dependency, must be a superkey.
Review of dependencies:
ClientID → FullName, Address, Phone, Email 
LoanID → ClientID, OfficerID, LoanAmount, InterestRate, Duration
RepaymentID → LoanID, DueDate, AmountPaid, AmountDue, Status
SavingsID → ClientID, Balance, AccountNumber, OpenDate
TransactionID → TransactionType, TransactionDate, Amount, LoanID, SavingsID
OfficerID → FullName, PhoneNumber, Email
No violations are present.
The schema meets the criteria for BCNF.

5. Final BCNF Schema (Cleaned)
Client(ClientID PK, FullName, Address, Phone, Email)
Loan(LoanID PK, ClientID FK, OfficerID FK, LoanAmount, InterestRate, Duration)
Repayment(RepaymentID PK, LoanID FK, DueDate, AmountPaid, AmountDue, Status)
SavingAccount(SavingsID PK, ClientID FK, Balance, AccountNumber, OpenDate)
Transaction(TransactionID PK, TransactionType, TransactionDate, Amount, LoanID FK, SavingsID FK)
LoanOfficer(OfficerID PK, FullName, PhoneNumber, Email)